olive oil
1 packet jasmine rice
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
2 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet sour cream
1 packet coriander

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with the boiling water.
• Add jasmine rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes. Drain.

• Meanwhile, drain sweetcorn.
• Discard any liquid from beef strip packaging. In a medium bowl, combine beef, All-American spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook corn kernels until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are “popping” out.

• Return frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and toss beef to combine.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Meanwhile, to the bowl with the corn, add shredded cabbage mix, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Divide jasmine rice between bowls.
• Top with All-American beef and charred corn slaw.
• Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese. Dollop over sour cream. Tear coriander to serve. Enjoy!